{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":800,"text":"In the year 1901,"},{"time":2640,"text":"a woman called Auguste was taken\nto a medical asylum in Frankfurt."},{"time":6960,"text":"Auguste was delusional"},{"time":8520,"text":"and couldn't remember\neven the most basic details of her life."},{"time":12280,"text":"Her doctor was called Alois."},{"time":15840,"text":"Alois didn't know how to help Auguste,"},{"time":18120,"text":"but he watched over her until,\nsadly, she passed away in 1906."},{"time":22520,"text":"After she died, Alois performed an autopsy"},{"time":25280,"text":"and found strange plaques\nand tangles in Auguste's brain --"},{"time":28520,"text":"the likes of which he'd never seen before."}]},{"cues":[{"time":30880,"text":"Now here's the even more striking thing."},{"time":34000,"text":"If Auguste had instead been alive today,"},{"time":37520,"text":"we could offer her no more help\nthan Alois was able to 114 years ago."},{"time":44080,"text":"Alois was Dr. Alois Alzheimer."},{"time":48520,"text":"And Auguste Deter"},{"time":50680,"text":"was the first patient to be diagnosed with\nwhat we now call Alzheimer's disease."},{"time":55680,"text":"Since 1901, medicine has advanced greatly."},{"time":59200,"text":"We've discovered antibiotics and vaccines\nto protect us from infections,"},{"time":63160,"text":"many treatments for cancer,\nantiretrovirals for HIV,"},{"time":67040,"text":"statins for heart disease and much more."},{"time":70896,"text":"But we've made essentially no progress\nat all in treating Alzheimer's disease."}]},{"cues":[{"time":78440,"text":"I'm part of a team of scientists"},{"time":80000,"text":"who has been working to find\na cure for Alzheimer's for over a decade."},{"time":83800,"text":"So I think about this all the time."},{"time":86280,"text":"Alzheimer's now affects\n40 million people worldwide."},{"time":90360,"text":"But by 2050, it will affect\n150 million people --"},{"time":96360,"text":"which, by the way,\nwill include many of you."},{"time":101040,"text":"If you're hoping\nto live to be 85 or older,"},{"time":105160,"text":"your chance of getting Alzheimer's\nwill be almost one in two."},{"time":111600,"text":"In other words, odds are\nyou'll spend your golden years"},{"time":114840,"text":"either suffering from Alzheimer's"},{"time":117080,"text":"or helping to look after a friend\nor loved one with Alzheimer's."},{"time":122480,"text":"Already in the United States alone,"},{"time":124480,"text":"Alzheimer's care costs\n200 billion dollars every year."},{"time":129919,"text":"One out of every five\nMedicare dollars get spent on Alzheimer's."},{"time":134680,"text":"It is today the most expensive disease,"},{"time":137840,"text":"and costs are projected\nto increase fivefold by 2050,"},{"time":141080,"text":"as the baby boomer generation ages."}]},{"cues":[{"time":144000,"text":"It may surprise you that, put simply,"},{"time":147400,"text":"Alzheimer's is one of the biggest medical\nand social challenges of our generation."},{"time":152760,"text":"But we've done relatively\nlittle to address it."},{"time":155960,"text":"Today, of the top 10\ncauses of death worldwide,"},{"time":159880,"text":"Alzheimer's is the only one\nwe cannot prevent, cure or even slow down."},{"time":167800,"text":"We understand less about the science\nof Alzheimer's than other diseases"},{"time":171520,"text":"because we've invested less time\nand money into researching it."},{"time":175240,"text":"The US government\nspends 10 times more every year"},{"time":179400,"text":"on cancer research than on Alzheimer's"},{"time":182400,"text":"despite the fact\nthat Alzheimer's costs us more"},{"time":186120,"text":"and causes a similar number\nof deaths each year as cancer."}]},{"cues":[{"time":191880,"text":"The lack of resources\nstems from a more fundamental cause:"},{"time":195640,"text":"a lack of awareness."},{"time":198600,"text":"Because here's what few people know\nbut everyone should:"},{"time":203360,"text":"Alzheimer's is a disease,\nand we can cure it."},{"time":208320,"text":"For most of the past 114 years,"},{"time":210880,"text":"everyone, including scientists, mistakenly\nconfused Alzheimer's with aging."},{"time":216360,"text":"We thought that becoming senile"},{"time":217861,"text":"was a normal and inevitable\npart of getting old."},{"time":221000,"text":"But we only have to look at a picture"},{"time":223040,"text":"of a healthy aged brain compared\nto the brain of an Alzheimer's patient"},{"time":226920,"text":"to see the real physical damage\ncaused by this disease."},{"time":230960,"text":"As well as triggering severe loss\nof memory and mental abilities,"},{"time":234840,"text":"the damage to the brain\ncaused by Alzheimer's"},{"time":237080,"text":"significantly reduces life expectancy\nand is always fatal."}]},{"cues":[{"time":242480,"text":"Remember Dr. Alzheimer\nfound strange plaques and tangles"},{"time":245560,"text":"in Auguste's brain a century ago."},{"time":248280,"text":"For almost a century,\nwe didn't know much about these."},{"time":252240,"text":"Today we know they're made\nfrom protein molecules."},{"time":255640,"text":"You can imagine a protein molecule"},{"time":257320,"text":"as a piece of paper that normally folds\ninto an elaborate piece of origami."},{"time":262160,"text":"There are spots\non the paper that are sticky."},{"time":264600,"text":"And when it folds correctly,\nthese sticky bits end up on the inside."},{"time":269560,"text":"But sometimes things go wrong,\nand some sticky bits are on the outside."},{"time":274040,"text":"This causes the protein molecules\nto stick to each other,"},{"time":277080,"text":"forming clumps that eventually become\nlarge plaques and tangles."},{"time":281680,"text":"That's what we see\nin the brains of Alzheimer's patients."}]},{"cues":[{"time":285240,"text":"We've spent the past 10 years\nat the University of Cambridge"},{"time":288360,"text":"trying to understand\nhow this malfunction works."},{"time":291800,"text":"There are many steps, and identifying\nwhich step to try to block is complex --"},{"time":296520,"text":"like defusing a bomb."},{"time":298600,"text":"Cutting one wire might do nothing."},{"time":300720,"text":"Cutting others might\nmake the bomb explore."},{"time":304160,"text":"We have to find the right step to block,"},{"time":306360,"text":"and then create a drug that does it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":309000,"text":"Until recently, we for the most part"},{"time":311080,"text":"have been cutting wires\nand hoping for the best."},{"time":313560,"text":"But now we've got together\na diverse group of people --"},{"time":316440,"text":"medics, biologists, geneticists, chemists,\nphysicists, engineers and mathematicians."},{"time":322040,"text":"And together, we've managed\nto identify a critical step in the process"},{"time":326280,"text":"and are now testing a new class of drugs\nwhich would specifically block this step"},{"time":330520,"text":"and stop the disease."}]},{"cues":[{"time":332360,"text":"Now let me show you\nsome of our latest results."},{"time":334880,"text":"No one outside of our lab\nhas seen these yet."},{"time":337560,"text":"Let's look at some videos of what happened\nwhen we tested these new drugs in worms."},{"time":342560,"text":"So these are healthy worms,"},{"time":344440,"text":"and you can see\nthey're moving around normally."},{"time":347560,"text":"These worms, on the other hand,"},{"time":350480,"text":"have protein molecules\nsticking together inside them --"},{"time":353600,"text":"like humans with Alzheimer's."},{"time":355240,"text":"And you can see they're clearly sick."},{"time":357560,"text":"But if we give our new drugs\nto these worms at an early stage,"},{"time":362560,"text":"then we see that they're healthy,\nand they live a normal lifespan."},{"time":367200,"text":"This is just an initial positive result,\nbut research like this"},{"time":370880,"text":"shows us that Alzheimer's is a disease\nthat we can understand and we can cure."}]},{"cues":[{"time":375640,"text":"After 114 years of waiting,"},{"time":378560,"text":"there's finally real hope\nfor what can be achieved"},{"time":380960,"text":"in the next 10 or 20 years."},{"time":384040,"text":"But to grow that hope,\nto finally beat Alzheimer's, we need help."},{"time":388920,"text":"This isn't about scientists like me --"},{"time":390800,"text":"it's about you."},{"time":392600,"text":"We need you to raise awareness\nthat Alzheimer's is a disease"},{"time":396200,"text":"and that if we try, we can beat it."},{"time":398840,"text":"In the case of other diseases,"},{"time":400680,"text":"patients and their families\nhave led the charge for more research"},{"time":403840,"text":"and put pressure on governments,\nthe pharmaceutical industry,"},{"time":406800,"text":"scientists and regulators."},{"time":409040,"text":"That was essential for advancing treatment\nfor HIV in the late 1980s."},{"time":413920,"text":"Today, we see that same drive\nto beat cancer."},{"time":418320,"text":"But Alzheimer's patients are often\nunable to speak up for themselves."},{"time":422680,"text":"And their families, the hidden victims,\ncaring for their loved ones night and day,"},{"time":427440,"text":"are often too worn out\nto go out and advocate for change."},{"time":431320,"text":"So, it really is down to you."},{"time":435720,"text":"Alzheimer's isn't,\nfor the most part, a genetic disease."},{"time":439080,"text":"Everyone with a brain is at risk."},{"time":442160,"text":"Today, there are 40 million\npatients like Auguste,"},{"time":446680,"text":"who can't create the change\nthey need for themselves."},{"time":449600,"text":"Help speak up for them,"},{"time":452080,"text":"and help demand a cure."}]},{"cues":[{"time":455346,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":456520,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}